# =============================================================================
# .gitignore for GROMACS MD simulation projects
# =============================================================================

# --- Large binary trajectory files (hundreds of MB to GB) ---
# NEVER commit these. Use institutional storage or Zenodo for archiving.
*.xtc
*.trr
*.edr
*.tng

# --- GROMACS binary run input files ---
*.tpr

# --- Checkpoint files ---
*.cpt
*.cpt.old
*_prev.cpt

# --- Coordinate output files (intermediate and final) ---
# Keep only your input PDB under version control
*.gro

# --- GROMACS topology fragments (auto-generated by pdb2gmx) ---
posre*.itp
topol*.itp

# --- Backup files auto-created by GROMACS when it overwrites ---
\#*\#

# --- Log files (stage logs in logs/ are fine to keep, mdrun logs are large) ---
md_*.log
nvt.log
npt.log
em.log

# --- Analysis scratch outputs (commit only final publication-ready ones) ---
*.xvg
*.xpm
*.eps

# --- Energy minimization convergence files ---
em.trr

# --- OS and editor noise ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.idea/
.vscode/

# =============================================================================
# What you SHOULD commit:
#   gromacs_md_pipeline.sh    ← the pipeline script
#   mdp/*.mdp                 ← all parameter files
#   input/*.pdb               ← input structure (if < 50 MB, else use Git LFS)
#   README.md
#   .gitignore
#   environment.yml or requirements.txt (if any analysis scripts)
# =============================================================================
